{"_id": "smeagol", "_rev": "23-0a61825cd3964d8415a346b64bcce292", "name": "smeagol", "time": {"modified": "2022-06-26T21:27:18.709Z", "created": "2015-01-21T08:41:26.880Z", "0.0.0": "2015-01-21T08:41:26.880Z", "0.0.1": "2015-01-21T08:58:24.655Z", "0.0.2": "2015-01-21T09:14:41.790Z", "0.0.3": "2015-01-27T01:33:58.645Z", "0.0.4": "2015-01-27T01:42:06.678Z", "0.1.0": "2016-05-28T16:52:18.218Z", "0.2.0": "2016-06-12T21:54:28.607Z"}, "maintainers": [{"name": "gserrano", "email": "contato@guilhermeserrano.com.br"}], "description": "A easy to use NodeJS http/https web-crawler.", "readme": "# Smeagol #\nSmeagol is a very simple NodeJS crawler module where you can create url patterns to extract different contents from different pages. \n\n## Install smeagol ##\n    npm install smeagol\n\n## How to use ##\n\n### Require Smeagol ###\n    var Smeagol = require('smeagol');\n\n\n### Instance and settings ###\n    let smeagol = new Smeagol(\n        {\n            crawl : [\n                {\n                    pattern_url : '^http://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/(.*)?$', \n                    id : 'news',\n                    each_item : '#glb-materia',\n                    find : {\n                        id    : '$(\".share-bar\").attr(\"data-url\")',\n                        title   : '$(\".entry-title\").text()'\n                    }\n                }\n            ],\n            limit: 6,\n            continuous : true,\n            maxConcurrency: 6,\n            domain : 'http://g1.globo.com/',\n            pattern_to_crawl : '^http://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/(.*)?$'\n        }\n    );\n\n\n\"pattern_url\" define what pages Smeagol will scrap.\n\"id\" is the identification for the result group in Smeagol results.\n\"each_item\" is a CSS selector. Smeagol will iterate this selector on the page and extract the data defined in \"find\".\n\"find\" is a object with label and CSS selector for each information you want to get from each \"each_item\".\n\n### Crawl ###\nJust start crawling!\n\n    smeagol.crawl({\n        uri : 'http://g1.globo.com/economia/'\n    })\n### Events ###\nSmeagol uses nodeJs events to let you decide what to do when you get the information you want to scrap.\n\n####complete(results)####\nEmitted when Smeagol complete scrapping or scrap the limit pages in settings.\n\n    smeagol.on('complete', function(results){\n        console.log(results);\n        console.log('Finished');\n    })\n\n####crawl(result)####\nEmitted every item (each_item in setting) Smeagol scrap. \n\nresult is a json object.\nurl is the page url where Smeagol scrapped the result.\n\n    smeagol.on('crawl', function(url, result){\n        console.log('crawl', url, result);\n    })", "versions": {"0.0.3": {"name": "smeagol", "version": "0.0.3", "description": "A easy to use NodeJS HTTP web-crawler.", "author": {"name": "Guilherme Serrano", "email": "contato@guilhermeserrano.com.br", "url": "guilhermeserrano.com.br"}, "main": "./index.js", "scripts": {"test": "echo \"Error: no test specified\" && exit 1"}, "repository": {"type": "git", "url": "http://github.com/gserrano/smeagol"}, "keywords": ["crawler", "scrapper"], "bugs": {"url": "https://github.com/gserrano/smeagol/issues"}, "engines": {"node": ">= 0.10"}, "dependencies": {"cheerio": "0.18.0", "http": "~1.3.10", "fs": "~1.3.10"}, "_id": "smeagol@0.0.3", "dist": {"shasum": "8837840e5bb967694ed7da52a7774f1023543788", "tarball": "https://registry.npmjs.org/smeagol/-/smeagol-0.0.3.tgz", "integrity": "sha512-4zmLWw57sj32vnB/9QFQPdux/t8p4VxfWCV0ehkIsluQyAxNUiUGJcqF5KwCglh/J1/hzFKdNnXofRN3YWXtoQ==", "signatures": [{"keyid": "SHA256:jl3bwswu80PjjokCgh0o2w5c2U4LhQAE57gj9cz1kzA", "sig": "MEYCIQDUc+O798/oE4PftZZLp8d2adBBFfG/O6Na7UkF/MIwmwIhALX7lSjnrO5Ghr/QJ2mJuzDXl6vrUOKlPLsemDXlgcD1"}]}, "_from": "./", "_npmVersion": "1.3.10", "_npmUser": {"name": "gserrano", "email": "contato@guilhermeserrano.com.br"}, "maintainers": [{"name": "gserrano", "email": "contato@guilhermeserrano.com.br"}]}, "0.0.4": 